  {
    "id": "alphabet",
    "title": "Turkish Alphabet & Pronunciation",
    "description": "Learn the 29 letters of the Turkish alphabet and their sounds",
    "difficulty": "beginner",
    "sections": [
      {
        "type": "explanation",
        "content": "Turkish uses a Latin-based alphabet with 29 letters. Most are pronounced as in English, but several special characters have unique sounds."
      },
      {
        "type": "table",
        "content": "Special Turkish Characters",
        "table": {
          "headers": ["Letter", "Sound", "Example"],
          "rows": [
            ["Cc", "j as in jump", "cam (glass) = jam"],
            ["Çç", "ch as in church", "çay (tea) = chai"],
            ["Ğğ", "silent, lengthens vowel", "dağ (mountain) = daa"],
            ["Iı", "uh as in about", "ılık (warm) = uhluhk"],
            ["İi", "ee as in feet", "bir (one) = beer"],
            ["Öö", "ur as in burn", "göz (eye) = gurz"],
            ["Şş", "sh as in shoe", "şeker (sugar) = sheker"],
            ["Üü", "ew as in few", "gül (rose) = gewl"]
          ]
        }
      },
      {
        "type": "explanation",
        "content": "Turkish is phonetically consistent — each letter always makes the same sound. Once you learn the alphabet, you can read any Turkish word correctly!"
      }
    ],
    "exercises": [
